Responsibilities : 
Proven ability to work with onshore and offshore teams. 
The ideal candidate should have a strong development background with recent management experience. 
Ability to work with Project Managers and others in the context of larger projects to ensure coordination of delivery; clear communication with stake holders; represent the development team to non-development professionals; obtain feedback back to the team; to represent the development team to external development organizations (counterparts). 
Scheduling Establishment of schedules, Sprint management, reporting on schedule, ensure visibility and transparency, ensure successful deployment and delivery. 
Expert knowledge of agile methodologies. 
Good knowledge of process development and release management 
Strong experience in team collaboration 
Expert knowledge of all phases of the SDLC 
Excellent written and verbal skills 
Deep understanding of business and technical processes and how they support clients? business 
Desire to grow yourself and others 
Ability to independently make decisions in the context of a larger strategic vision. 
Team player where not afraid to jump on issues for quick resolutions 
API experience is a MUST 
Cloud experience a plus 
Apigee experience is a plus 
Financial experience is a plus 
